[{"location":"reference/#Reference","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#DiscreteNaturalNeighbors","page":"Home","title":"DiscreteNaturalNeighbors","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for DiscreteNaturalNeighbors.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"tutorial/#Tutorial","page":"Tutorial","title":"Tutorial","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/","page":"Tutorial","title":"Tutorial","text":"This tutorial demonstrates the use of the DiscreteNaturalNeighbors.jl package for the interpolation of a function from an unstructured grid in n gtreq 2 dimensions.","category":"page"},{"location":"tutorial/#2D-interpolation","page":"Tutorial","title":"2D interpolation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/","page":"Tutorial","title":"Tutorial","text":"We first look at a 2D interpolation problem and define some function that we want to interpolate","category":"page"},{"location":"tutorial/","page":"Tutorial","title":"Tutorial","text":"using Plots, DiscreteNaturalNeighbors\n\nfunction f2D(x,y)\n    return 0.1*(y-1)^2 / ( 2 + abs(x)^2)^2 + exp(-0.2*(y-x^2)^2) + exp(-0.4*(y-x)^2) * sin(0.25*(0.2*x^2+y)^2) + 1.2*exp(-((x+2)^2)/0.2 - (y-3.5)^4)\nend\n\nxRange, yRange = -5:0.1:5, -5:0.1:5\n\nfun_vals = [f2D(x, y) for x in xRange, y in yRange]\nheatmap(xRange, yRange, transpose(fun_vals), clim=(minimum(fun_vals), maximum(fun_vals)))","category":"page"}]
